cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the generalization of deep neural networks. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it studies the behavior of neural networks. Additionally, since the paper discusses the performance of deep networks in image classification tasks, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper proposes a new complexity measure for deep networks, which could fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, since the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
